  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity Building for Preparing and Responding to COVID-19 Pandemic in Border Provinces of Viet Nam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Government of Viet Nam and provincial public health authorities have requested IOM provide technical expertise and assistance with securing funds to support frontline ports of entry (POEs) officials to better respond to the ongoing public health threats from neighbouring countries. The proposed project will undertake an assessment to identify gaps and needs at POEs in selected provinces that share borders with neighbouring countries. Based on assessment findings and consultations with relevant stakeholders, IOM will develop a list of needs of personal protective equipment and other essential supplies for procurement and distribution to POE officials and migrants in project provinces. IOM will support POE officials to enhance their preparedness and response through provision of training on infection prevention and control methods with PPE as well as necessary measures to protect migrants in vulnerable situations, especially women and children, with an emphasis on upholding the dignity and the right to privacy of migrants. The proposed project will contribute to effective control of COVID-19 transmission in border areas by strengthening the capacity of frontline officials working at POEs.</narrative>
  </description>
